post_text:
AVID (@avid4college) STUDENT OF THE WEEK!

Zeriah E. - 10th Grade AVID Student

Motivation:
My future and my family motivates me because I want to make my family proud and I also want to have a good and successful life.

Strategy for success:
Note-taking is a strategy that has helped me succeed in school. I use the notes that I take in class to review, prepare for test, and it gives me extra practice.

College/Career Plans:
After high school, I plan on attending college with scholarships and grants that I have earned. I would like to pursue a career in physical therapy because I love helping people and it is something that I am really great at.

post_text:
Hey Wsst Family,

Mountain Park's Diversity Site Councils bridge organizations
and individuals to support each others missions and empower
our community. For the last nine years, summit attendees made
time for human connection and challenged the ordinary
through the day of storytelling. The annual summit reminds us
that our collective work truly does matter and inspires us to
continue building for today and tomorrow.

Since we are forgoing the traditional in person gathering to
keep everyone safe and healthy during the pandemic, we hope
this virtual storytelling will further cultivate a sense of belonging
and build upon the bridges between us to better support our
community.

If you feel inspired to join the virtual bridge, you can click the link below and submit your story.

https://sway.office.com/bXSl4m0OV6IefXwk?ref=email

post_text:
Hey WSST Family,

We have some GREAT news share. A for Arizona announced today that Western School of a Science and Technology is one of the 18 public K-12 school systems that will receive Expansion and Innovation Fund grants to innovate and reimagine how best to serve their students in the 2020-2021 school year. Round One grants were funded by an initial $1 million contribution from Governor Duceys Emergency Education Relief (GEERs) fund through federal CARES Act monies to improve access to high-quality teaching and learning this school year.

The grants recognize innovations and promising practices that support student populations that have been significantly disrupted during the global COVID-19 pandemic.

Thank you to everyone helped and supported Western throughout the process.

Click the link below to read the full press release.

https://www.aforarizona.org/2020/08/06/a-for-arizona-announces-round-one-of-2020-expansion-and-innovation-fund-grant-recipients/

#Innovation #vamoswarriors #AforArizona

post_text:
Hey Wsst Family,

WSST plans to move forward with a start date of August 3rd, not August 17th, with full online learning. There are multiple reasons to make this decision. First, we must always prioritize student learning, and the sooner students are back in classrooms, even virtually, the sooner we can continue teaching and learning. Second, our community relies upon our services -meals, counseling, social work, and more. Third, the Governors orders did not waiver the 200-day requirement, and so WSST students would need to make up those days at the end of the 20-21 school year. We remain committed to providing students the needed preparation for the academic rigors of college graduation leading to career success. We also remain committed to the safety of our staff, students, and families.

A survey was sent out via Remind today. We would like to gauge your readiness to return to campus after August 17th given this information. Please complete this survey by Friday, July 10th.

Please expect more details in the coming days.

Hey Wsst Family,

In a response to the rapidly expanding numbers of Coronavirus in Arizona and the need for additional testing, American Legion Travis L. Williams Post 65 is teaming up with the HeroZona Foundation to host free drive-through Covid-19 testing in the parking lot of South Mountain Community College, July 9-10.

The event is open to all members of the community, and no pre-registration or appointment is necessary. A valid ID is required to be tested. No previous symptoms are required to be tested. The event is drive-through, so no walk-ups will be admitted. Testing takes place while supplies last.

https://www.southmountaincc.edu/events/2020/drive-through-covid-19-testing

Message from the WSST football coaches:

We want to take a few minutes to showcase our Seniors Football Players.

Many of the seniors have been part of our school and team since middle school.

Together we have accomplished great things, with only 3 years as a Varsity Football Program:
-1 Real Sports Combine Championship
-1 Real Sport Combine MVP (Adan)
-1 Highland Prep Passing League Championship
-1 Highland Prep Big Man Championship
-1 CAA Vinny Award/Sportsmanship Athlete of the Year (Ernesto)
-1 CAA Vinny Award/Sportsmanship Athletic Director of the Year
-1 CAA Coaches Spotlight of the Month Recognition
-10 CAA All State Players
-2 Semi Final Appearances
-2 Fiesta Conference/Region -Championships
-Winning Record of 17-4
-First NAIA College Football Offer -Scholarship to Adan Z.
-First HJCAC College Football Offer to Osvaldo R.

Thank you for everything you have done for Western, Maryvale, and Our Warrior Family.

We love you! Maryvale Proud! Warrior Strong! Vamos Warriors! - From Coaches #VamosWarriors #SeniorWeek2020

To help reduce the likelihood of any COVID-19 spread among members of our campus community, we will be
extending our Spring Break until at least Friday, March 27, 2020. School will remain closed during that time. This also means that all extracurricular activities such as clubs
and sports will be canceled until further notice.

Please see Founding School Director Mr. Peter Boyles UPDATED letter (English/Spanish) to our families.

You can also access the letter by clicking the link below.
https://western.teamcfa.school/school/updated-coronavirus-disease-2020-covid-19-letter-to-our-families/

Hey Wsst Family,

You are invited to participate in our Arizona Tax Credit Donation Campaign. If youre unfamiliar with the tax credit, when you file your state tax return, you receive a dollar-for-dollar reduction in the amount of taxes you owe (up to $200 per individual or $400 per married couple filing jointly) if you support Western: CFAs arts, athletics, and extracurricular programs!

To donate, you can Drop off a check, made out to WSST or Click the link https://western.teamcfa.school/about/donate-now/
#VamosWarriors

post_text:
Hey Wsst Family,

Western School of a Science & Technology has been designated an AVID Schoolwide Site of Distinction. This honor is awarded to a small subset of AVID school campuses that have demonstrated outstanding commitment to their students.

This distinction illustrates a commitment to equity and opportunity for all students on a campus. It also promotes rigorous academic opportunities for students throughout the campus, while showing a commitment to superb instructional practices across the school.

Arizona Charter Schools Association
